# LaTeX Document Structure

## Requirement

All LaTeX documents SHALL follow a basic document structure with proper ordering of elements.

LaTeX documents SHALL begin with a `\documentclass` declaration.

Package imports SHALL appear after the `\documentclass` declaration and before the `\begin{document}` command.

Document content SHALL be placed between `\begin{document}` and `\end{document}` commands.

## Structure

LaTeX documents SHALL follow this basic structure:

```latex
\documentclass[options]{class}

% Package imports
\usepackage{package1}
\usepackage{package2}

% Document metadata and settings
\title{Document Title}
\author{Author Name}

\begin{document}

\maketitle

% Document content

\end{document}
```

## Rationale

Consistent document structure:
- Improves readability and maintainability
- Makes it easier for developers to navigate LaTeX documents
- Follows LaTeX best practices and conventions
- Reduces errors from misplaced commands

